    Product Description

    Funny & Clever

    Your very own wearable medical meme, this funny one-piece pin is sure to inspire smiles and laughs from coworkers and patients alike with it's healthcare work humor!

    Pin It Anywhere

    Display your personality with this small, decorative accent featuring a shiny black pager and punny message. Great brooch for badges, lapels, bags, clothes, and backpacks!

    Perfect Size

    Created to make a statement and start a conversation, this small pin will not impede your space or drag down your badge.

    Durable & Easy-to-Clean

    Made with durable nickel and enamel, this pin is waterproof and easy-to-clean with a quick sani-wipe after work, especially important in healthcare environments.

    "Attention all hospital personnel – code brew in the break room. Repeat, code brew." Our Coffee Pager enamel pin arrives stat to your doorstep via Amazon Prime. And with it's cute and clever message, we've honestly never been happier to hear the pager go off. Hot or iced, it's your choice and the perfect gift for a coffee-obsessed and caffeine-loving nurse, student, respiratory therapist, technologist, paramedic, physician assistant, doctor, and many more.

    Dimensions 0.8 inches tall by 1.2 inches wide
    Weight 0.14 ounces
    Materials Raised black nickel filled with hand-painted soft enamel in vibrant colors
    Securement Black rubber backing

    More Pins PRN is your one-stop shop for healthcare-inspired enamel novelties, as needed. A special line of pins from All Night Apparel, these tiny tokens are creatively designed by a critical care nurse and meant to inspire love, laughter, and positive vibes in the hearts and minds of our healthcare workers. We'd love for you to shop small from a woman-owned business this season! Find us and our growing pin collection on Instagram at @morepinsPRN.

    From the brand

    Previous page

    3. How did we get our start?

      In 2021, Rachel founded More Pins PRN as a (literal) sister company to All Night Apparel, owned and operated by her twin brother, Brian. Rachel was (and still is) a critical care nurse working in the ICU during the pandemic, and wanted to design a line of pins that specifically honored the healthcare community.

      Why do we love what we do?

      Working in the current climate of healthcare is hard, period. So if there is even the teeniest tiniest way to recognize that shared experience and somehow bring a smile to it, we find ourselves fulfilled.

    4. What makes our products unique?

      Our designs are special because they are entirely home-grown. Before becoming a nurse, Rachel did graphics work, allowing her to develop an idea from point of inspiration to finished product – all from a corner of her home office. And by partnering with her brother, this small business is also a family one too.

      What problem are we solving?

      If laughter is the best medicine, then love and appreciation is a close second in terms of treatment modalities. We hope to bring a little dose of both to the table, in the form of our enamel novelties.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
